Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, Osun State has suspended a lecturer at the Centre for Distance Learning, Mr. Monday Omo-Etan, for allegedly sexually molesting a 19-year-old female student. The institution’s spokesman, Abiodun Olarewaju, made this known in a statement given to reporters. The statement read: “Less than three weeks after the management of Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife expressed its zero tolerance for sexual harassment by investigating and suspending a lecturer in the Department of International Relations, Mr. Olabisi Olaleye, the university has again suspended a lecturer at the Centre for Distance Learning for sexually molesting a 19-year-old female student. “The university has handed over the suspect, Mr. Monday Omo-Etan, to the police. “The management has restated its commitment to the eradication of sexual harassment, molestation and other social vices. “It will be recalled that the management received a report of the investigative panel constituted to look into the allegation of sexual harassment against Mr. Olabisi Olaleye, a lecturer in the Department of International Relations, on January 28, 2020.” 